{
  "text": "DXA measures the areal density (not the volumetric density) corresponding to the ratio between bone mineral content and the area of scanned bone. The relatively high predictability of BS by aBMD could be partially explained by the fact that bone size is indirectly involved in DXA measurements [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
